comments.body:
@rhatdan There's already a "Kernel Version Requirements" section in install.md -- this PR was a correction in that section.  Our local team lost days ferreting this out, and I'm hoping to help other buildah adopters avoid the same pitfall. 

@vrothberg Why the close?  What needs to be improved in order to get this accepted?

If the choice is to not require specific kernel versions, then it might be better to remove the "Kernel Version Requirements" section completely, or at least remove any mention of version numbers from that section and instead describe required features. 
 The "4.0" version number that is in that section right now is misleading.
